<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc27b5366-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s314"><num value="314">§ 314.</num><heading> Central Office</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The Central Office of the Department shall be in the District of Columbia.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc27b5367-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s2/a">Pub. L. 102–83, § 2(a)</ref>, <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/383">105 Stat. 383</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idc27b5368-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idc27b5369-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="priorProvisions" id="idc27b536a-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Prior Provisions</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Prior section 314 was renumbered <ref href="/us/usc/t38/s1114">section 1114 of this title</ref>.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Provisions similar to those in this section were contained in <ref href="/us/usc/t38/s230/a">section 230(a) of this title</ref> prior to repeal by <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s2/a">Pub. L. 102–83, § 2(a)</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
